Oct 24 2009 	Here is how to get around construction	Yes, the construction is a pain. The first connecting street behind(east) the resort is Audrie. This street connects with Tropicana by going through the MGM property. There are lots of speed bumps and make sure you don't get in the right taxi lane. It comes out on Tropicana and you can go either east or west(towards the strip) depending on which side of the exit you are in. If you choose to go the next street east of Audrie which is Koval, be aware that they are tearing up the intersection and Koval between Harmon and Tropicana is down to one lane both ways. Unless you are in the very slow time of the day I would NOT risk it-take Audrie. In any case, allow for more travel time and yes it is an inconvenience but I do not consider it a major reason to not stay at the Marriott.The resort itself is very nice-as someone else said it is not pretentious. I would not consider it to be 5 Star either in ambience or accomodations. Certainly upscale, comfortable, clean, convenient and blissfully quiet. Great views of the strip. I can't imagine someone would be dissatisfied unless they are looking for a) Excitement b) A great pool scene or c) Over the top luxury. The pool as others have stated is small but there was no fight over lounges as I have had in other locations. Expect to see children in what essentially is a kids wading pool. This is a place where families will spend a week with children in tow.Depending on the price, I would certainly stay there again.	
