Mar 5 2009 	Great location and all the amenities you could want in a suite	We stayed in a one bedroom suite for a week in February 2009 and were very pleased! We've always stayed at hotels (MGM, TheHotel, Rio, Luxor, TI, Excalibur, even Stratosphere once to check it out) so were hesitant at what my timeshare could offer us in Vegas. A great big space with everything we needed in a perfect location is what we got! The entire suite is decorated in brand new, clean sunny modern sort of country french design (don't worry, it's not frilly or flowered). The kitchen is fully stocked for all your needs - I made dinner for two and even breakfast for six one morning. Special note - if you are making bacon do it in the microwave. There's no real exhaust for smoke which resulted in us setting off the really loud smoke alarm but hotel staff responded IMMEDIATELY with friendly and very nice assistance.The dining room seats 6 comfortably. The living room has a comfortable couch, two chairs, and tables and a flat screen TV with a ton of cable channels. We actually stayed in once or twice to relax and watched a movie or two - very nice. The entire hotel has free WiFi - a nice touch that really came in handy. The bedroom is huge, with another big tv, comfortable bed with nice linens and good pillows, well lighted vanity area, and a really big two person jacuzzi. The separate bathroom has a two person, two shower head shower that was awesome. Our view out the bedroom and living room was of City Center on the strip and the side of Planet Hollywood and beyond - including a slice of the Bellagio fountains. My only gripe is that there is no full length mirror - come on, it's a must for getting dressed up for a night out in Vegas! The rooftop has a bar (open 11am to 6pm) with several tables and chairs, and 6-8 person hot tub and a small but fine sized pool (open from something like 7am to 11pm) with lounge chairs. We liked the day and night view from the roof - you can bring up your own wine and chill out while watching most of the Strip lights, from Mandalay Bay up to Caesar's and beyond. There's also a 24-hour fitness center but between Vegas fun and the ultra comfort of our suite, we never quite got there to check it out. As for location - this place is right behind the Harley Davidson Restaurant &amp; parking lot located on the corner of Harmon and the Strip, across from the new City Center. Unless you cannot walk 90 seconds of a block, there is no reason to call this hotel &quot;off the strip.&quot; Think of it this way - if you are staying &quot;on the strip&quot; at the MGM, you enter on the strip and then have to walk to the back of the hotel to check in or get to elevators so you've just walked 2 blocks indoors. At the Marriott, you are simply not walking through a casino. And if you chose not to walk the short block up to the Strip, but instead to cross Harmon Ave, you can enter Planet Hollywood &amp; the shops through a side door located directly across (i.e., about 50 feet) from the Marriott's entrance. Marriott guests can use Planet Hollywood's pools and gym for free too. Check out Planet Hollywood's players club - when you join you get a ridiculous amount of free drink &amp; $$ off the buffet coupons as well as free food and retail coupons. With the free drink coupons alone, we saved over $100! Also check out Planet Hollywood's buffet (since the Marriott does not have any restaurants). We were pleasantly surprised by how good the PH buffet was - the dessert bar even has cotton candy!Overally, Marriott Service was friendly and professional. Valet parking attendants and bellhops were great. One of them even gave us the name and number of a nightclub hostess who hooked us up with VIP service and a private table at Ghostbar at the Palms later that week. Score!	
