Feb 24 2009 	Comfort location 	We are Marriot owners and traded out a 2br in Ft. Lauderdale for a 1br at the Grand Chateau and were quite pleased. Well appointed and decorated. Kitchen and bathroom were roomy, and with quality appliances and fixtures. Check in and check out was a breeze, and the staff was very helpful...especially when I pulled the dumb guy move and forgot it was Valentines day...(...we were in Vegas after all...all the days run together). Anyway, Paul...I think that was his name...at the concierge jumped through hoops to help me out...I mean, save my butt! As most reviewers have said the location is ideal. 1 block off the strip, which definately cuts down on the noise. (see my photos) Also, all the other reviews were very helpful regarding groceries, etc...so I won't rehash all that. We were in town for a photogaraphy conference which was being held at the MGM and it was maybe a 10 minute walk to get there. Bally's is about 15 minute walk...the show at the Jubilee Theater is a must...traditional Vegas! During our stay I'd estimate occupancy was only about 30% so it was very quiet. The weather was cold 35 -45 degrees, and windy with occasional showers. Pretty crummy weather, but the bar on the roof was open a few hours during the day...the bartenders weren't happy to be there...can't blame 'em I guess, I hate cold weather too! I just ordered more cocktails and enjoyed the view...the view from the rooftop is incredible! Great for photos! Again, as most reviewers have said the pool is small...there weren't many people in while we were there and I certainly wasn't going to venture in..although it is heated. I'll include a good picture of the rooftop. I really only have one suggestion...don't use the ice in the freezer's automatic ice maker. Dump it out in the sink, wash the bin, and use the public ice machine...on our floor it was right by the elevators. I live in Costa Rica and think I've got an iron stomach...but it wasn't enough to combat the water in Las Vegas. All in all, as I said at the top we were quite pleased, and when we get back to Vegas we'll be staying at the Chateau.	
Feb 19 2009 	Time Share with Great Location and Service	First off, this property is a Marriott Timeshare so dont expect full service amenities such as a restaurant, room service, etc. However this property does offer complimentary valet and bell service and has a small marketplace with goodies and Starbucks coffee and Concierges to help you with your vacation activities.We had a guest unit/studio. This was alright for us for just 2 nights. The unit had a small frig, microwave, sink, plates, glasses, and coffee maker. The guest unit has a king bed. We found the unit to be really clean and comfortable. The guest unit has an ordinary shower. Not the &quot;his and hers&quot; shower heads in the Master Villa.Valet service was quick despite the long line of people checking out after a Presidents Day weekend. They worked their hardest to get our vehicle. The property has a shuttle which can take you to the Fashion Show Mall on the north end of the strip near Treasure Island and Wynn/Encore. Shuttle driver knew all the shortcuts to get around the parking lot that is the Strip.Used the concierge service and never once was asked to attend a timeshare presentation. Thank goodness! We already own at Marriott Canyon Villas in Phoenix and dont need another week.The property had a gym with treadmills, weights, elliptical machines, and bikes. Steam rooms in the locker rooms. Nice equipment. Internet service is wireless.For tickets to shows, I recommend going to &quot;Tickets 4 Tonight&quot; which has various store fronts on the Strip. Actually there is one about a block away from this property. Ask the concierge where the closest location is. We used this to get 2 for 1 tickets to see Louie Anderson stand up comedy. We also saw that they sold discounted tickets to &quot;O&quot;, Elton John, Love, Cris Angel, Blue Man Group, Excalibur Knights of the Round Table, etc. The only problem is that they give you a voucher and you have to run over to the box office for the show that you are seeing to get a seat assignment. They also sell discounted passes to buffets. I recommend that you stop here if you come to Vegas.	
