) for a basic cleaning service(s) that was charged to vacation club owners every day. Combine the excessive yearly maintenance fees + daily cleaning fees + $25,000 (with interest)= rip off scam! As if the $25,000 wasn't enough, by the time you add the daily cleaning fees together with the yearly maintenancefees you'd be paying well over $100. a day for a vacation you already paid for in advance. In the long run you save no money buying into a timeshare with Marriott. The Marriott Grand -Chateau was nice, but not nice enough for the price per night.	
