Sep 10 2007 	Plus and Minus	This is a beautiful property in a great location. The staff is attentive and friendly. The rooms are fresh and comfortable. The following points can be a plus or minus depending on what you want: The entire property is &quot;no smoking&quot;, it's a time-share so there is no restaraunt, the pool is on the roof and very small and simple, you need to walk or get a cab to get anywhere. It's not a casino so you have to leave the property to gamble. There is very little for children to do and the customers are generally middle aged or older. One tower is completed, the second is constructed and the work going on is inside so noise is at a minimum, HOWEVER, as the third and fourth tower are constructed, the noise will be major and the workers start at 4:30 AM. When the property is completed, there will be a spa and a large pool. The lobby will double or triple in size and other amenities will be added. The best part of this property is the location: MGM is on one side and Planet Hollywood is on the other side. The strip is only steps away. The Chateau is at the South End, which is the most desirable part of the strip. Overall, it's a great place to stay if you want to stay at a quiet, classy place but be near the action. If you need two or three bedrooms and a full kitchen and laundry, nothing beats the Chateau. Remember, this is a time share so if you rent a room you will get maid service. If you buy or trade into it, you have to pay as much as $50 per day to get the room cleaned. You can also just clean it yourself. As I said, my comments are here not to give you an opinion but to give you facts so you can decide for yourself if this is the type of property you might be interested in. I would stay there again but not until the majority of the construcion is completed. Happy Traveling!	
Sep 1 2007	It's OK	This hotel wasn't my 1st choice, but it's what was available as an exchange through my timeshare company. For Vegas, it's considered small. The location was actually great - right around the corner from the strip, so it was accessible to everything, and right across from the Planet Hollywood Miracle Mile Shops. I know most people that go to Vegas, spend very little time at the hotel, but when you want a little down time, there needs to be something to make you want to stick around. Unfortunately, there wasn't anything here like that. The pool (located on the roof on the 38th floor) was very small - about 12 feet long only 3 feet deep. It had a bar, but no snacks, so if you were hungry, you needed to leave the hotel to get food, as the hotel itself had no restaurant either. Thank goodness there was music piped in from a radio (at the pool, that is), otherwise there was no other atmosphere. The hotel was very clean, and the staff was friendly and knowledgeable. The room wasn't bad, although a bit small. I don't know what their actual prices are, so I can't say if it's worth the money, but as I said, if you want location, it's great.	
Aug 29 2007	Awesome hotel with beautiful rooms and a great staff!	We stayed here from June 30th-July 7th, 2007. The hotel is absolutely beautiful and our room was gorgeous. We noticed a minimal amount of noise from the construction, but it did not bother us at all (although we have 2 small children so our tolerance level might be higher than some - lol). The staff was so friendly and went out of their way to make sure we had everything we needed. Anytime we asked for something, the staff was very friendly and accommodating. The room was clean and had everything we could ask for in it. The rooftop pool was a bit small and always filled with kids, but our kids enjoyed it and as the building expands, another pool/pools will be added. The only downside was that the bar on the roof was extremely overpriced for purchasing drinks. If you plan to drink, go to the 7-11 a few blocks away on the Strip or just go gamble at one of the casinos and get them for free! My family and I loved this hotel and would definitely return.	
Aug 6 2007 	Great property rooms 	Stayed here Jul 29 - Aug 5 in a 1 bedroom suite - full kitchen, separate bedroom. The room was nicely decorated and everything looked new and shiny! The lobby/common areas were also very nice, although the rooftop pool is small and there is no shade. Staff was very polite and attentive. Location is great - one block away from the masses on the Strip.There is construction going on all around: this property and Plant Hollywood across the street. We stayed on the 31st floor, facing Harmon St. (even-numbered rooms) and barely heard a thing - our sleep was never interrupted. The rooms that face the other side (odd-numbers) are right next to the construction of the new tower, and might have more of a noise problem. So, to recap, aim for a high floor and an even-numbered room.	
Jul 31 2007 	Super Location	The resort is under construction (like the rest of the city) but they do a good job in keeping the lobby and guest areas clean and quiet. The lobby and rooms are top notch. The pool is inadequate for a resort of this type...no shade, very few chairs and a small area. Go next door to the Planet Hollywood hotel (there is reciprocity). They have two large pools and a huge sunbathing patio. It is also a better location to people watch.The best part about this resort is the location. You are only a half block from the strip and located next to Planet Hollywood (formerly Aladdin). You are very close to NYNY, MGM, Bellagio and Paris. The best bit of advice we picked up on this site was regarding show tickets. Do not buy in advance. Just up the street from the Marriott in the Hawaiian square shopping area is a kiosk that sells 2 for 1 show tickets. They open everyday at 11:00am and have a monitor which lists the available shows and prices. Most are 1/2 price, but some of the more popular shows are available at 1/3 off. All of the shows were available when we were there...Carrot Top, Mamma Mia, Zumanity, etc. Unless you are not flexible or are absolutely set on one particular show, you should definitely buy tickets from the kiosk.The only complainants other than the pool would be with the lack of a restaurant in the hotel. Other than overpriced food from the gift shop, there were no choices. Again though, because of the location you can walk across the street to the Miracle Mile shops and choose from 8-10 restaurants.	
Jul 22 2007 	Very nice experience!	We just got back from a 3-night stay and had a fabulous time! After reading other reviews, I was very concerned about construction noise but it was not a problem at all. They're mostly finished with the exterior of the second tower, so the work is primarily being done inside now. We did hear a little bit of noise occasionally, but certainly not enough to bother us. The two towers will connect at the elevator lobby, so they were working on that area on our floor. Other floors didn't have that construction. So if you're worried about the noise, ask for a room where they're not working on that lobby maybe.The location is great - we were able to walk to the strip in less than 5 minutes, and we were right by Planet Hollywood (and the Miracle Mile shops, as mentioned by a previous reviewer!). The view from the rooftop bar was awesome. We didn't use the pool (rooftop, also), but it looked nice, if a little small. We were told upon check-in that they have a reciprocal agreement with the Polo Towers and Planet Hollywood so we could have used either of those pools as well.In all, an excellent vacation in a quality property.	
